# Features of Scripta.io

- [b No set-up] . Create a new document with the click of a button. Then start typing.

- [b Web-based] . Scripta produces web pages, not PDFs, although you can do that too.

- [b Instant rendering] . As you type, the web pageyou are working on — text, images, equations, cross references, table of contents, etc. — is updated. All in real time.

- [b Modern editor] . Click on a word in the rendered text.It will be highlighted in the source text. Selectsome source text, type ctrl-S. The corresponding rendered text will be highlighted. Type ctrl-1 to remove thehighlight.

- [b Available everywhere, anytime] . Your writing is available to you, your students, and your colleages anywhere there is an internet connection. Readable on smart phones, tablets, laptops, and desktop computers.

- [b No vendor lock-in] . Philosophically, we are opposed to vendor lock-in. It is wrong. Practically, we provide tools for you to export both individual documents and yourentire corpus of documents. See XXX. Additionally,the Scripta compiler, which is open source, is avaiable on [link Github https://github.com/jxxcarlson/scripta-compiler-v2] .

- [b Integrated image uploader] . Click on thecamera icon for placing images in your document. Paste the image into the uploader, then paste the resulting image block in the editor.

